commit.title: rpmbuild.yml: don't run mock as root
commit.message:
rpmbuild.yml: don't run mock as root

https://github.com/osbuild/osbuild/commit/a52e256c481c00e61f785f3ad68e29e1ac8a09fb
introduced running osbuild's test in the %check phase of an rpm build.
A lot of osbuild's tests are gated on $UID == 0 (i.e. running as root).
Thus, if $UID != 0, then a lot of tests are intentionally skipped.

RPM building setups (koji, mockbuild.sh in this repository) usually run
mock as a non-root user, thus the tests get skipped. However, this
script actually runs mock as root, and thus these tests don't get
skipped, causing a lot of failures because there are missing tools
in the buildroot, some rootful tests require networking, or they cannot
run in an environment missing certain privileges.

This commit changes the playbook to run tasks as root only when they
require it (subscription-manager, dnf). Mock is no longer run as root,
aligning the rpm building process to what's common in other setups.

commit.title: go.mod: update images to v0.209.0
commit.message:
go.mod: update images to v0.209.0

In adapting to the new osbuild/osbuild-exec code, ExportPaths got
dropped. This variable / option was not used anywhere anyway.

Changes with 0.209.0
----------------
  - gitlab: run ostree manifest generation and builds only when needed (osbuild/images#1961)
    - Author: Achilleas Koutsou, Reviewers: Simon de Vlieger, Tomáš Hozza
  - osbuild/osbuild-exec: extract building the osbuild cmd to helper (osbuild/images#1963)
    - Author: Sanne Raymaekers, Reviewers: Achilleas Koutsou, Simon de Vlieger
  - rhel10: add ism secret & top secret oscap profiles (HMS-9507) (osbuild/images#1962)
    - Author: Gianluca Zuccarelli, Reviewers: Lukáš Zapletal, Sanne Raymaekers

commit.title: gitlab: only update github status at the end of the pipeline(s)
commit.message:
gitlab: only update github status at the end of the pipeline(s)

Updating the statuses on GitHub at the end of each job causes the
statuses to show failure when the jobs are still running.  In osbuild
and images we instead have a finish stage that runs the
update_github_status.sh script either with the 'finish' argument, if
everything succeeded, or with a 'fail' argument, if anything in the
pipeline failed.  This makes sure that the statuses on GitHub are only
updated at the end of the pipeline runs.

statuses to show failure when the jobs are still running.  In osbuild
and images we instead have a finish stage that runs the
update_github_status.sh script either with the 'finish' argument, if
everything succeeded, or with a 'fail' argument, if anything in the
pipeline failed.  This makes sure that the statuses on GitHub are only
updated at the end of the pipeline runs.

commit.title: CI: run testing on RHEL 9.8 and 10.2 nightly (HMS-9226)
commit.message:
CI: run testing on RHEL 9.8 and 10.2 nightly (HMS-9226)

Some issues that previously prevented us from using GCP for RHEL-10 or
running installer tests on 10.1 should be presumably resolved, so
adjust the respective test cases.

Update osbuild ref in Schutzfile to the latest `main` `HEAD`, to get 9.8
and 10.2 RPM builds.

Signed-off-by: Tomáš Hozza <thozza@redhat.com>

Some issues that previously prevented us from using GCP for RHEL-10 or
running installer tests on 10.1 should be presumably resolved, so
adjust the respective test cases.

Update osbuild ref in Schutzfile to the latest `main` `HEAD`, to get 9.8
and 10.2 RPM builds.

Signed-off-by: Tomáš Hozza <thozza@redhat.com>
